    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2001 Acura Integra Type R, a definitive benchmark in front-wheel-drive engineering. This example features the legendary B18C5 powerhouse, a hand-ported inline-four that delivers a visceral 8,400 RPM redline and seamless VTEC engagement. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise close-ratio five-speed manual transmission and a factory-spec helical Torsen limited-slip differential for unparalleled turn-in response. The chassis remains structurally pristine, retaining all original factory reinforcements and weight-reduction measures. Finished in iconic Championship White with all matching VIN tags and impeccable paint depth, this vehicle offers a pure, analog driving experience that is mechanically flawless.",
